<div id="review_4085951735" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4085951735" />
    <a title="Jeff Mayo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/879889-jeff-mayo"><img alt="Jeff Mayo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1308976943p2/879889.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4085951735?book_show_action=true">Jun 29, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Mayo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Mayo" href="/user/show/879889-jeff-mayo">Jeff Mayo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781426418365" href="/book/show/1719304.The_Crisis">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4085951735" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15642102760701461708">There are a couple of things you have to be able to do in order to read historical fiction. The first thing is, you have to accept that these fictional characters are going to have chance encounters with a lot more real people than would be possible. Once you get past that, you get a nice glimpse at what Missouri was like during the Civil War. There&apos;s a lot about Lincoln, which I liked, but most of this is pulp that isn&apos;t necessary.</span>
  <span id="freeText15642102760701461708" style="display:none">There are a couple of things you have to be able to do in order to read historical fiction. The first thing is, you have to accept that these fictional characters are going to have chance encounters with a lot more real people than would be possible. Once you get past that, you get a nice glimpse at what Missouri was like during the Civil War. There's a lot about Lincoln, which I liked, but most of this is pulp that isn't necessary.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15642102760701461708" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

