<div id="review_1103183036" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1103183036" />
    <a title="Paul Thillen" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36818220-paul-thillen"><img alt="Paul Thillen" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1579487964p2/36818220.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1103183036?book_show_action=true">Nov 10, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul Thillen" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul Thillen" href="/user/show/36818220-paul-thillen">Paul Thillen</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781426418365" href="/book/show/1719304.The_Crisis">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1103183036" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18187544721433488177">Revisionist history at its finest. Cheesy love story built around the American Civil War as experienced in St. Louis, full of one dimensional characters, Forrest Gump quality coincidences and happy slaves that love their masters.<br/><br/>Important to read only to see how time changes the view of a war and to see how racism is casually found in popular literature.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


